He thought about cooking a nice, meaty, white-tail soup.
He was running through the dark, fleeing from the sight of hunting demons, and he was thinking about soup. He’d never cooked a white-tail soup before in his life. He’d never even thought about it. Maybe he had in passing, but it was never something that he couldn’t get past. His mind’s eye was filled with a vision of flaky white meat spiced with bitter herbs, all swimming in a creamy yellow broth.</Notes>
